:: StoryTitle
Asylum Jam 2014


:: Start
First day at work and I'm already behind. There's a new kid starting tomorrow and I forgot to fill out the rest of his papers. If don't make sure his papers are filed before the secretary comes in it wont look good. 

That secretary at the principal's office didn't exactly seem like the forgiving type. Perhaps she was hired back when... well before they took down all the religious stuff. Not that I'd mind a place with a little more discipline.

I just hope the one key they gave me will open the main doors.

:: found documents
Here we are. 

...

Seems more or less in order actually, I just need to write in the proper classes for little Mr. Baumann's first time here.

Wait a minute. Baumann... that's a bit of a coincidence. Not many German descendants around here. Could he be related to Anne? I mean the age is right for a young son I suppose. But she'd had to have given him her name. No, it says both his parents are former students here. 

Anne was my best friend in school, and I we didn't go to this one. And [[why|documents2]] on earth would she return to this town with her family?

<<unity 'STORY' stopMovement "">>

Stacks of old yellowed papers. Someone moved them recently.

It's almost all prayers. Guides for the teacher, which hymns goes with each day, how to handle difficult questions and things like that.

Hmm... this one is called: [["Procedures for specially devout students"|look papers]]

There's no one here.

:: look papers2
"Only the student whose fickle mind is as smooth and cold as our dear St. Nim are ready."

"Once the mind is ready the body must follow. If their ears distract them with jokes and sweet music they must be cut."

"A mouth filling with more than nourishment demands must be sown shut. Likewise the eyes that linger too long on the pleasing shapes and colors of creation."

"Only when the wings of His little angels are properly clipped will they carry their prayers to His withered ears."

----

What the hell is this!? Did they really do this to the kids? 

Too many people in this town are involved with the church. If this gets out there's no telling where it would lead!

[[I have to get out of here!|get out]]


:: First
"Alright I think I have Jim on the line. So do you have a question for our guest this evening?"

"Yeah thanks, Linda. No questions from me but I have a thing or two that suit in your studio needs hear. I've lived in this town all my life and I have nothing but good things to say about our church. They've run that school for as long as it's been there. They built it for Christ's sake! ... pardon. Now I don't believe in all that hocus pocus, mind, but if listening to a few fairy tales means our kids stay out of trouble that's fine by me!"

"Well that's one way to look at it I suppose. What do you think about that Mr. Williams?"

"Well Linda..."

----

Ugh. I can't stand listening to that guy...

:: essays2
Okay this is strange.

"First application for advanced class 1C by Anne Baumann."

It's a few copies of completed tasks and a motivational letter with more than a few mentions of St. Nim. Nothing but praise and longing for his holy, crippled abstinence. I mean this was a religious school back then... but still.

"Searching for God with eyes ever closed."
"... clipping my sinful wings."
"Mortal ears cannot hear the quiet call of the stone."

Crazy, and nothing like Anne at all!

Plus, there's no 'advanced class 1C' here. I dont think there ever was. The kids are assigned class rooms 1-5 A or B.  A down here and B upstairs.

:: remember nightmare
I guess it's only to be expected that I'd get a bad dream. Took me much too long to find a job. And I'm taking a bit of a chance going back to my home town. I mean I may never leave now.

But it felt so real. The rows of stones. Tall and dark, just like the old slab down at the church, but darker, smoother. I swear I can still feel the cool marble against my hand...

My heart is already racing again. Just need to get it out of my mind. Tomorrow will be a much better day I'm sure. If I just get those papers fixed. [[It should be up on the corner any minute...|go to school]]
